  "elements": [
    {
      "id": "ZotyrIM2A5NfzvbUUJPwB",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 253,
      "y": 147,
      "width": 1255.3990478515625,
      "height": 775,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1967326767,
      "version": 1888,
      "versionNonce": 607581441,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1774033765087,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Way how 2 different microservices communicate:\nExample microservice A wants to communicate with microservice B\n\n1) Service discovery capability :\n- Microservice A wants to communicate with Microservice B. Then it needs its location(IP address and Port number)\n- Service discovery functionality is required so that Microservice A can get the location of microservice B different instances.\n\nScenario 1 : Service discovery returns all the Microservice B instance location.\nScenario 2: service discovery returns address of load balancer of Micro service B location.\n\n2) Load balancing capability.\nBased on both the scenarios we need to decide load balancer which will be client side.\n\n3) Authorization & Authentication\nWe need to authorize and authenticate between each even though they are internal.\n\n4) Circuit breaker capability :\nWe can control failures to some specific micro service.\n\n5) Re-try capability\nIf request to some micro services fails then some issue can be retryable.\n\n6) Deployment strategy\nDifferent strategies are like Canary, Red-black, Blue-Green etc.\n\n7) Telemetry capability\nWe need capability to collect data which will help in analysis and monitoring of a component.\n\n\nInstead of all these we have Service Mesh.\nWe have sidecar proxy which is present with the pod and has all these capabilities. It can be controlled by control panel.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 768,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Way how 2 different microservices communicate:\nExample microservice A wants to communicate with microservice B\n\n1) Service discovery capability :\n- Microservice A wants to communicate with Microservice B. Then it needs its location(IP address and Port number)\n- Service discovery functionality is required so that Microservice A can get the location of microservice B different instances.\n\nScenario 1 : Service discovery returns all the Microservice B instance location.\nScenario 2: service discovery returns address of load balancer of Micro service B location.\n\n2) Load balancing capability.\nBased on both the scenarios we need to decide load balancer which will be client side.\n\n3) Authorization & Authentication\nWe need to authorize and authenticate between each even though they are internal.\n\n4) Circuit breaker capability :\nWe can control failures to some specific micro service.\n\n5) Re-try capability\nIf request to some micro services fails then some issue can be retryable.\n\n6) Deployment strategy\nDifferent strategies are like Canary, Red-black, Blue-Green etc.\n\n7) Telemetry capability\nWe need capability to collect data which will help in analysis and monitoring of a component.\n\n\nInstead of all these we have Service Mesh.\nWe have sidecar proxy which is present with the pod and has all these capabilities. It can be controlled by control panel.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
